# Zim:fw configuration This is not sourced  #
# during shell startup Run `zimfw install`  #
# to add new modules, `uninstall` to prune, #
# or `update` to get latest versions.       #
# ========================================= #

#
# EARLY MODULES
# -------------
# Sets sane Zsh built-in environment options
zmodule environment
# Aliases and PATH management for Homebrew
zmodule homebrew
# Provides handy git aliases and functions
zmodule git
# Setup mise
zmodule joke/zim-mise
# Applies correct bindkeys for input events
zmodule input
# Sets a custom terminal title
zmodule termtitle
# Utility aliases and functions Adds colour to ls, grep and less
zmodule utility

# NOTE: Normally new modules should be added here ⬇️
# Check each module documentation for any caveats

#
# PROMPT INFO
# -----------
# Exposes how long the last command took to run to prompts
# zmodule duration-info
# Exposes git repository status information to prompts
zmodule git-info
# Exposes working directory path to prompts
zmodule prompt-pwd

#
# PROMPT THEME
# ------------
# A heavily reduced, ASCII-only version of the Spaceship and Starship prompts
# zmodule asciiship
# A minimal prompt with limited info (needs git and pwd mods)
zmodule minimal

#
# COMPLETION
# ----------
# Additional completion definitions for Zsh
zmodule zsh-users/zsh-completions --fpath src
# Enables and configures smart and extensive tab completion, must be sourced
# after all modules that add completion definitions
zmodule completion

#
# LATE MODULES
# ------------
# Fish-like syntax highlighting for Zsh, must be sourced after completion
zmodule zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting
# Fish-like history search for Zsh, must be sourced after
# zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting
zmodule zsh-users/zsh-history-substring-search
# Fish-like autosuggestions for Zsh Add the following to your ~/zshrc to boost
# performance: ZSH_AUTOSUGGEST_MANUAL_REBIND=1
zmodule zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions
